WEBVTT

00:02.125 --> 00:05.166
<i>- You're demented.
- Previously on St. Elsewhere.</i>

00:05.233 --> 00:08.250
You building that nest
for you and Jane?
[ Caws ]

00:08.317 --> 00:11.754
good-Bye, my high-Flying bird.
My eagle.

00:11.821 --> 00:15.091
Guns aren't allowed
in the hospital.
Well, tell that to patients.

00:15.157 --> 00:17.493
I had a "Gomer"
In here yesterday
with a sawed-Off Shotgun.

00:17.560 --> 00:22.231
Leslie Stevenson wanted
a career, so she put everything
on hold until it was too late.

00:22.298 --> 00:25.000
<i>I don't want that
to happen to me.
Then don't you let it.</i>

00:25.067 --> 00:29.004
Can you take care of yourself,
the baby and Ralph?

00:29.071 --> 00:32.775
<i>- We deserve a chance.
- [ Beale ]
  it's rough out there, Jane.</i>

00:32.842 --> 00:35.177
<i>- [ Ralph ] don't worry.
 I won't screw up.
- [ mews ]</i>

00:35.244 --> 00:38.647
[ screaming ]

00:39.815 --> 00:42.485
<i>- Stop!
- Tonight on st. Elsewhere.</i>

00:47.656 --> 00:50.826
You doctors today,
you're spoiled, you're selfish.

00:50.893 --> 00:53.596
You might as well be a lawyer
or an accountant.

00:53.662 --> 00:56.465
[ squawking ]

00:56.532 --> 00:59.168
Why were you quacking
around mrs. Pechar's room?

01:01.404 --> 01:03.672
White's kid.
She ate some mothballs.

01:03.739 --> 01:06.809
I can remember when Myra
couldn't wait for me
to get home at night.

01:06.876 --> 01:08.878
And now she can't stand
for me to touch her.

01:08.944 --> 01:12.148
- You know something?
You're a jerk.
- Actually, I'm lithuanian.

02:41.237 --> 02:43.105
<i>[ thunderclap ]</i>

02:49.078 --> 02:51.514
<i>now, listen, honey.
When you empty a urinal,</i>

02:51.580 --> 02:53.983
you've got to be sure to record
the exact volume...

02:54.050 --> 02:56.185
on the patient's
"I" and "0" Sheet.

02:56.252 --> 03:00.322
Now miss Barlow
is gonna have to start
all over again.

03:00.389 --> 03:02.558
<i>[ sighs ]</i>

03:02.625 --> 03:06.295
I don't do floors,
and I don't do ceilings.

03:15.337 --> 03:17.373
Were your car windows open?
Yeah.

03:17.440 --> 03:19.809
The back seat
looks like niagara falls.
Oh!

03:19.875 --> 03:22.178
Mrs. Valente is Stabilized.
Poor woman.

03:22.244 --> 03:24.880
What happened to her?
Somebody threw her off
a trans-Dyke overpass.

03:24.947 --> 03:26.916
She says whoever did it's gonna
try and finish the job.

03:26.982 --> 03:30.453
So you keep an eye on her.
Let me know
if there's any change.

03:32.021 --> 03:34.256
Renal Has tried everything
there is to try.

03:34.323 --> 03:36.525
So for the last five
of his 45 years,

03:36.592 --> 03:40.763
Mr. Brennan has been
on thrice weekly
maintenance hemodialysis...

03:40.830 --> 03:43.466
because
of end-Stage renal failure,

03:43.532 --> 03:46.135
secondary to
a presumptive diagnosis...

03:46.202 --> 03:48.738
of chronic nephritis.

03:48.804 --> 03:54.376
So, you see, medical therapy
has failed completely.

03:54.443 --> 03:58.614
That's where we move in.
We've already inserted
the Gore-Tex graft.

03:58.681 --> 04:01.250
When you insert the graft,
you'll feel a thrill...

04:01.317 --> 04:03.452
because of
the increased force...

04:03.519 --> 04:06.822
from the direct
artery-To-Vein insertion.

04:08.824 --> 04:11.327
Rounds started 15 minutes
ago, Ehrlich.

04:11.394 --> 04:13.329
Were you catching up
on your beauty sleep?

04:13.396 --> 04:17.600
No, actually,
I sprained my pinky.

04:17.666 --> 04:19.969
Sprained your pinky?

04:20.035 --> 04:24.407
How?
I was playing handball
this morning.

04:24.473 --> 04:28.744
[ groans ]

04:28.811 --> 04:31.814
I want to see you in my office.
10:00.

04:31.881 --> 04:37.486
Mr. Brennan is a prime candidate
for a kidney transplant.

04:37.553 --> 04:40.990
<i>First, we have to find
one of his relatives
with a matching--</i>

04:41.057 --> 04:43.692
<i>[ continues, indistinct ]</i>

04:47.630 --> 04:50.166
what's up?

04:50.232 --> 04:52.835
I'm behind on
my student loan payments.

04:52.902 --> 04:55.638
They're threatening
to take me to court.

04:55.704 --> 04:57.640
Oh, come on.

04:57.706 --> 05:00.609
They must send out 50,000
of these as a scare tactic.

05:00.676 --> 05:02.611
It works.

05:02.678 --> 05:06.682
By the time
they actually find you,
you'll be retiring to Santa fe.

05:06.749 --> 05:11.153
The hospital received an INQUIRY
about my salary.

05:11.220 --> 05:13.189
How behind are you?

05:17.893 --> 05:20.763
See you later, okay?
Okay.

05:23.632 --> 05:26.335
Don't worry.

05:28.437 --> 05:31.507
I'm sorry.
The doctors here
do not make house calls.

05:33.576 --> 05:35.978
<i>You're gonna have to--</i>

05:36.045 --> 05:38.981
<i>Well, don't you have
your own internist?</i>

05:39.048 --> 05:42.118
<i>Look, you're going to
have to hold, all right?</i>

05:42.184 --> 05:44.387
Jack, can you take this call?
Who is it?

05:44.453 --> 05:46.555
Some Guy.
Says he has to have a doctor.

05:46.622 --> 05:48.791
He's been tying up the line
for 20 minutes.

05:48.858 --> 05:51.961
He says it's an emergency.
Hello?

05:52.027 --> 05:54.163
Yes, I'm a doctor.

05:54.230 --> 05:56.132
Well, come down
to the Hospital.

05:57.291 --> 06:01.195
Yeah.
No personal phone calls,
please.

06:01.261 --> 06:03.397
Guy wants a doctor.
He called the right place.

06:03.464 --> 06:05.499
No, I can't come
to your apartment.

06:05.566 --> 06:09.269
I'll send an ambulance.
I wouldn't go unless
it was Jane Fonda,

06:09.336 --> 06:11.572
Ralph Nader
or Michael internicola.
What?

06:11.638 --> 06:14.274
Who's Michael internicola?
My best friend
from grade school.

06:14.341 --> 06:17.511
I assure you,
paramedics are qualified.

06:18.545 --> 06:20.781
Okay. Okay.

06:20.848 --> 06:22.783
Yes, I promise I'll be
the one who comes.

06:22.850 --> 06:25.886
Can you cover for me?
I'm gonna make a house call.

06:25.953 --> 06:29.690
A house call? Morrison,
house calls are obsolete,
like rotary engines.

06:29.757 --> 06:32.259
Not only that,
they're impractical,
they're time-Consuming.

06:32.326 --> 06:36.029
- You're liable
to get a parking ticket.
- I'm on my way.

06:40.100 --> 06:42.403
- Anybody got an umbrella?
- No.

06:42.469 --> 06:45.773
No.
[ Muttering ]

06:45.839 --> 06:48.275
Good.

07:13.734 --> 07:16.937
<i>[ man ]
who?
It's Dr. Morrison.</i>

07:19.640 --> 07:21.875
A Mr. Lukovic called me
about an emergency.

07:21.942 --> 07:23.877
I'm lukovic. Took you
long enough to get here.

07:23.944 --> 07:27.881
The streets are flooded.
You said you were dying.

07:37.858 --> 07:41.762
I'm Dr. Morrison.
What's your name?

07:41.829 --> 07:44.398
<i>Claudia Lynch.
She's a mute.</i>

07:48.902 --> 07:51.839
<i>Every two minutes,
she's on the Toilet.</i>

07:53.373 --> 07:56.009
Open. Ahh.

07:57.845 --> 08:01.281
<i>She's dehydrated.
What's making her sick?</i>

08:01.348 --> 08:03.584
- I don't know.
- You said you were a doctor.

08:03.650 --> 08:06.420
- Are you a relative of hers?
- I live on the next block.

08:06.487 --> 08:08.422
<i>You should've brought her
in to the hospital.</i>

08:08.489 --> 08:10.891
We have the equipment down there
to make a proper diagnosis.

08:10.958 --> 08:14.027
<i>Has she ever had
stomach problems before?
No.</i>

08:14.094 --> 08:18.999
- Has she ever had trouble with
her pancreas or Gall bladder?
- Not that I know of.

08:19.066 --> 08:21.869
What was she doing just before
the pain started?

08:21.935 --> 08:23.837
I don't know.
She was like this
when I got here.

08:27.574 --> 08:30.844
What's this?
Eggnog.

08:30.911 --> 08:32.880
Homemade.

08:42.789 --> 08:44.792
Does she take medication
for anything?

08:44.858 --> 08:46.794
She's always been as healthy
as an athlete.

08:46.860 --> 08:51.298
- What are you looking for?
- Might be food poisoning.

09:03.077 --> 09:08.382
One of these is for nausea,
the other for diarrhea.

09:08.449 --> 09:10.417
Get them filled
as quickly as possible.

09:10.484 --> 09:13.887
Haven't got anything with you
to give her now?

09:13.954 --> 09:17.825
There are a million
different drugs
on the market, Mr. Lukovic.

09:17.891 --> 09:20.627
My Bag's too small
to bring all of them.

09:23.497 --> 09:26.533
Don't get out of bed
unless you have to.

09:26.600 --> 09:28.669
Drink a lot of water.

09:28.736 --> 09:34.341
No food, no more
of that eggnog, okay?

09:36.677 --> 09:40.080
How much do I owe you?
Don't worry about it.

09:40.147 --> 09:42.316
She's sick, you came.
What's that worth to you?

09:42.382 --> 09:45.352
Well, to be perfectly honest,
I don't know.

09:45.419 --> 09:48.455
I've never made
a house call before.
Let's forget it.

09:48.522 --> 09:51.625
You're not doing us
any favors here.
We pay for what we get.

09:51.692 --> 09:57.030
Here's 20.
Is that enough?
Yeah, that's fine.

09:57.097 --> 09:59.733
If she isn't better by tonight,
bring her in to st. Eligius.

10:11.445 --> 10:14.548
<i>- [ Craig ] I thought you
 wanted to be a surgeon.
- I do, sir. Very much.</i>

10:14.615 --> 10:19.119
It takes
a special kind of commitment,
a unique discipline.

10:19.186 --> 10:22.890
One might say a higher order
of self-Sacrifice.

10:22.956 --> 10:26.760
Because when
a properly trained surgeon
enters the professional Arena,

10:26.827 --> 10:30.164
he becomes an indispensable
part of American health care.

10:30.230 --> 10:32.232
I know, and I'm
really sorry I was late.

10:32.299 --> 10:35.135
Tardiness is not the issue here.

10:35.202 --> 10:38.739
Though if it ever happens again,
I'll ship you back to berkeley
in an avocado crate.

10:38.806 --> 10:42.609
- Yes, sir.
- Ehrlich, what's
the most important tool...

10:42.676 --> 10:46.747
that a surgeon has
in the operating room?

10:46.814 --> 10:48.782
Um--

10:48.849 --> 10:51.885
- The most important tool?
- After his mind, of course.

10:51.952 --> 10:55.022
Aha. Well, uh--

10:55.089 --> 10:57.257
Hands.

10:57.324 --> 11:00.594
- His hands.
- Hands. Of course.

11:00.661 --> 11:02.863
<i>There are very few careers
that depend more...</i>

11:02.930 --> 11:05.532
<i>on the use of your hands
than ours does.</i>

11:05.599 --> 11:08.368
<i>A concert pianist, Maybe.
 A sculptor, sure.</i>

11:08.435 --> 11:11.105
I see what you're saying.
What I'm saying is...

11:11.171 --> 11:13.540
that when you're in
the middle of an operation...

11:13.607 --> 11:17.478
and the scrub nurse screws up
or the RESIDENT
becomes squeamish,

11:17.544 --> 11:21.081
you'll be able to help
that patient through
because of these.

11:21.148 --> 11:24.384
<i>I mean, you can study
for years and years
and years,</i>

11:24.451 --> 11:26.587
and then because of some
stupid little mistake...

11:26.653 --> 11:29.389
like slicing the BREAD wrong
or picking up a box...

11:29.456 --> 11:33.093
or going for a kill
in a handball game,
and it's over.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.429
<i>Finished.
Forever.</i>

11:35.496 --> 11:38.365
Now, I didn't waste
all this time on you...

11:38.432 --> 11:40.601
just to have you
throw it away.

11:40.667 --> 11:44.605
- Do I make myself clear?
- Yes, sir.

11:44.671 --> 11:46.807
Now, I'm gonna give you
a little motto...

11:46.874 --> 11:52.179
that the head of surgery,
Dr. David domedion,
said to me in my residency.

11:52.246 --> 11:55.849
"When you're going into O.R.,
wash your hands.

11:55.916 --> 11:59.453
<i>When you're coming out,
watch your hands."</i>

11:59.520 --> 12:03.223
<i>Got it?
Yes, sir. I've got it.</i>

12:03.290 --> 12:06.326
Now get outta here.
I've got a lot of work to do.

12:10.330 --> 12:13.901
<i>[ Ralph squawking ]
hurry up. Hurry.
He's here.</i>

12:13.967 --> 12:17.371
Oh, Ralph!
Ralph, get down from there!

12:17.438 --> 12:21.742
It's cold.
The water's coming in.
[ Squawking continues ]

12:21.809 --> 12:25.179
it's okay.
[ chattering, indistinct ]

12:26.513 --> 12:29.249
now, Ralph, I want you
to get down!

12:29.316 --> 12:32.519
[ Shouting ]

12:32.586 --> 12:36.857
call Dr. Beale.
Tell him Ralph's
on the loose again.

12:36.924 --> 12:39.293
Ralph, get down!

12:52.673 --> 12:54.675
Jerry Fauvell was telling me
about his new Girlfriend.

12:54.742 --> 12:58.045
He described her as a cross
between Judy Garland
and Liza minnelli.

12:58.112 --> 13:00.914
If you ask me, old Jerry
doesn't have both of
his chopsticks in the suey.

13:00.981 --> 13:03.383
Love is Blind.
Lust has 20-20 Vision.

13:03.450 --> 13:06.887
Hey! Easy on the bucks,
Wingding.

13:06.954 --> 13:10.224
Look at this mess.
Multiple rib fractures,

13:10.290 --> 13:15.295
three on the Louie and a 20%
underlying pneumothorax.

13:15.362 --> 13:18.665
This guy wants to be
outta here by saturday
to play Tennis with his boss.

13:18.732 --> 13:22.536
What did Dr. Scabrini say?
He glanced at the x-Rays
for two seconds.

13:22.603 --> 13:26.373
"You oughta learn to
trust yourself more, fycus."

13:26.440 --> 13:30.344
"Fycus." Are you lost,
mrs. Levenson?
Yeah.

13:30.411 --> 13:32.946
Will you hold it for me?
All right.

13:37.518 --> 13:40.521
Excuse me.
Could you take care
of this woman for me?

13:40.587 --> 13:42.756
Yes, Doctor.
Thank you.

13:44.324 --> 13:46.994
[ Groans ]

13:47.060 --> 13:49.196
god!
Excuse me.

13:49.263 --> 13:52.933
Next stop, first floor.
Stomachs, spleens,
descending colons.

13:55.502 --> 13:58.305
Catch you later.
Bye.

13:58.372 --> 14:00.741
Did the cops ever catch
the guys that mugged you?
Nope.

14:00.808 --> 14:02.743
At least you got
your credit cards back, huh?

14:02.810 --> 14:05.646
My mastercharge was last seen
sunning itself in Bermuda.

14:05.712 --> 14:08.215
How much did they charge
on the cards?
Six thousand so far.

14:08.282 --> 14:10.384
I wish I had those creeps
in front of me right now.

14:10.451 --> 14:12.453
Oh, yeah?
What would you do?
Take a snapshot?

14:12.519 --> 14:14.988
That's the worst part of it all.
I know I should've
done something.

14:15.055 --> 14:17.791
Hey, man, when they got you
from behind, they got you.

14:17.858 --> 14:20.994
I keep thinking,
"I should've done this.
I could've done that."

14:21.061 --> 14:25.532
It's like every time
I come in here, I wonder
if it's gonna happen again.

14:27.201 --> 14:30.104
Okay, your lung
is partially collapsed.

14:30.170 --> 14:33.540
If the volume decreases
any more, we're gonna have to
put a tube in your chest.

14:33.607 --> 14:36.877
So I think you'd better forfeit
Saturday's match.

14:36.944 --> 14:39.546
If it does, I'll be ready.
Nobody's gonna
catch me off guard again.

14:39.613 --> 14:42.082
Norah, you wanna
give this guy a ride?

14:42.149 --> 14:44.151
Makes you so angry.
Yeah, sure it does.

14:44.218 --> 14:47.621
But what's the difference
if some Hood takes your money
or some OIL sheikh does?

14:47.688 --> 14:50.124
I get ripped off
every time I go
in the supermarket.

14:50.190 --> 14:53.460
What, with my wife, my kids,
my student loans.

14:53.527 --> 14:55.462
Did you know one of the muggers
put his mug on my
driver's license,

14:55.529 --> 14:59.767
and he's flashing it
all over greater Boston
as positive I.D.?

15:01.635 --> 15:03.537
all right, who's next?

15:05.305 --> 15:07.641
Come on, Jack.
The waiting room's s.R.O.

15:07.708 --> 15:09.843
Mr. Lukovic--

15:10.878 --> 15:12.813
Listen to me.

15:12.880 --> 15:15.182
I can't. I'm busy.

15:15.249 --> 15:18.552
I have a lot of people here
I have to see.

15:21.088 --> 15:23.690
What do you mean
the baby can't breathe?

15:25.092 --> 15:27.528
Where's the mother?

15:27.594 --> 15:31.098
Uh-huh. I get it, yeah.

15:33.267 --> 15:36.603
[ sighs ]
I get off in half an hour,
Mr. Lukovic.

15:38.605 --> 15:41.608
Uh, sure, I'll see you then.

15:41.675 --> 15:44.278
Sooner if possible.

15:44.344 --> 15:47.648
Uh, 24 claremont,
apartment 7-C.

15:47.714 --> 15:50.417
Yeah, I got it.

15:50.484 --> 15:53.220
The guy with a concussion
is starting to talk crazy.

15:54.421 --> 15:58.325
The woman you intruded upon
was mrs. Pechar.

15:58.392 --> 16:01.061
She's made a formal complaint
to Dr. Westphall.

16:01.128 --> 16:04.665
You know, Ralph,
he may just feel it's about time
to clip your wings.

16:04.731 --> 16:09.436
[ Clears Throat ]
Ever since Jane left, I'll admit
I've been a bit depressed...

16:09.503 --> 16:12.906
and acting
somewhat peculiar.

16:12.973 --> 16:15.476
But now I've had this
extraordinary Revelation.

16:15.542 --> 16:17.678
Revelation?
About what?

16:17.745 --> 16:19.813
I've discovered the root
of my problem.

16:19.880 --> 16:24.551
I've been staring in the mirror
instead of looking
out the window.

16:24.618 --> 16:27.688
I've been too wrapped up
in the Saran of my own reality.

16:27.755 --> 16:33.060
I'm gonna find a way
to reach beyond
the narrow vision of my psyche.

16:33.127 --> 16:36.263
I want to cross
the mighty hemisphere and become
an ACTIVE participant...

16:36.330 --> 16:39.967
in the great pageant
of human intercourse.

16:40.033 --> 16:43.704
As the beatles said,
"We all live
in a yellow submarine."

16:43.771 --> 16:45.706
All of us.

16:45.773 --> 16:48.342
Any ideas as to how
you'll accomplish your goal?

16:49.643 --> 16:51.879
No, not yet.

16:51.945 --> 16:54.448
One must first
work out a clear plan,

16:54.515 --> 16:56.517
establish a primary focus...

16:56.583 --> 17:00.421
and then apply a carefully
thought-Out methodology.

17:00.487 --> 17:03.157
I respect your opinion
greatly, Hugh,

17:03.223 --> 17:06.026
so if you have any suggestions,
feel free to let me know.

17:06.093 --> 17:08.362
I'll do that, Ralph.

17:08.429 --> 17:10.798
I will.
More coffee?

17:10.864 --> 17:12.800
Uh, no, thanks.

17:12.866 --> 17:17.337
There's, uh-- there's still
one thing that I don't
quite understand as yet.

17:17.404 --> 17:19.973
What's that?

17:20.040 --> 17:22.709
Why were you quacking around
mrs. Pechar's room?

17:22.776 --> 17:27.448
It was clearly time to Herald
my revelation to the World.

17:37.057 --> 17:39.827
Hey.
What is that?

17:39.893 --> 17:43.397
Cha Xiu Bao
from King Wah's. Mmm.

17:43.464 --> 17:47.167
I always keep one handy
in case I need an M.S.G. Fix.

17:47.234 --> 17:50.104
Where you going on
such a dismal, dreary day?

17:50.170 --> 17:52.306
Another house call.

17:52.372 --> 17:56.343
You've got a severe g.S.C.,
Morrison.
I left my Rosetta stone at home.

17:56.410 --> 17:59.012
What's a g.S.C.?
g.S.C.--
Good samaritan complex.

17:59.079 --> 18:02.416
You made the mistake
of reading the fine Print
on your hippocratic oath.

18:02.483 --> 18:06.019
Uh-huh.
Let me tell you
a little story, boy-O.

18:06.086 --> 18:08.789
A "Truth is
stranger than Fiction."
is it short?

18:08.856 --> 18:12.326
These two doctors
are attending a party
at a plush Palm springs Hotel.

18:12.392 --> 18:16.263
Drs. Kildare and Casey--
We'll call 'em--
Are summoned to the next room.

18:16.330 --> 18:18.265
A woman has gone into
cardiac arrest.

18:18.332 --> 18:22.703
I mean, she's throwing six
P.V.C.'s and dropped a beat
for 15 seconds.

18:22.770 --> 18:25.539
Casey and kildare are getting
set to start C.P.R....

18:25.606 --> 18:27.808
When two paramedics
rush in.

18:27.875 --> 18:31.512
The four of them can't agree
on which procedure to use
and start slugging each other.

18:31.578 --> 18:35.482
A policeman shows up, looks over
the situation and starts
clubbing kildare and Casey.

