easy for them--
Wait a minute.

34:48.956 --> 34:51.391
What are you talking about?
You having a nervous breakdown?

34:51.458 --> 34:55.161
I wish I was.
A nervous breakdown would be
a breeze compared to this.

34:55.228 --> 34:58.065
To what?
Thinking about my life.

34:58.132 --> 35:01.535
I'm beginning to think
maybe I got off the bus
a few stops early.

35:01.602 --> 35:04.004
Do you know I was the only kid
in my boy scout troop,

35:04.071 --> 35:07.808
maybe the whole B.S.A.,
that never tried
to get a merit badge?

35:07.875 --> 35:10.711
I took an "F" In Chaucer
rather than apologize
to my professor...

35:10.778 --> 35:15.682
for saying he didn't
speak middle english
very well.

35:15.749 --> 35:18.919
I don't know.
Maybe I am having
a nervous breakdown.

35:18.986 --> 35:20.921
You're just having
a bad day. That's all.

35:20.988 --> 35:22.923
No, when westphall
was chewing me out,

35:22.990 --> 35:25.559
it was like the principal
was taking my bowling ball away.

35:25.626 --> 35:27.561
I don't like authority.

35:27.628 --> 35:30.697
Like it or not,
westphall is right.
Doctors don't carry guns.

35:30.764 --> 35:32.933
That's easy to say.
You're not going into
emergency Medicine.

35:33.000 --> 35:37.137
Don't give me that.
I've been in E.R.
Just as long as you have.

35:37.204 --> 35:39.506
I've been knocked around
down there.
I didn't go out and buy a gun.

35:39.573 --> 35:41.942
Phil, I'm gonna spend
my life down there.

35:42.009 --> 35:44.912
I've always only wanted
to work in the emergency room.

35:44.978 --> 35:47.314
It's got excitement.
You know, vitality, chaos.

35:47.381 --> 35:50.050
There's nothing like it
anywhere else in the hospital.

35:50.117 --> 35:52.586
A guy can be a bandit down there
and still do some Good.

35:52.653 --> 35:56.123
What am I gonna do now?

35:56.190 --> 35:59.626
I'm scared.
I'm scared to go back in there.

35:59.693 --> 36:01.628
Listen to me.

36:01.695 --> 36:05.866
We're all scared, Wayne.
Scared of one thing or another.

36:05.933 --> 36:09.536
You know, sometimes I go
into a restaurant
or any room anywhere...

36:09.603 --> 36:11.538
and every face I see is white.

36:11.605 --> 36:13.607
There's people
who hate me right off the bat...

36:13.674 --> 36:15.943
just for being black,
who would wanna kill me.

36:16.009 --> 36:18.412
I don't even know who for sure.

36:18.479 --> 36:20.914
But I gotta be prepared
for a wisecrack...

36:20.981 --> 36:23.784
or a fistfight.

36:23.851 --> 36:25.919
But you know what I do?

36:25.986 --> 36:28.155
I stand in that doorway,

36:28.222 --> 36:30.390
I suck it in,

36:30.457 --> 36:32.426
and I keep walking
right to my table.

36:59.253 --> 37:01.922
Wanna buy a gun?
[ Laughing ]

37:03.857 --> 37:06.560
<i>[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]
[ Woman ]
mmm.</i>

37:06.627 --> 37:09.897
<i>This is so nice.
[ Morrison ]
enjoy it.</i>

37:09.963 --> 37:12.266
<i>I have to leave
for the hospital
in an hour.</i>

37:12.332 --> 37:14.835
<i>[ Phone ringing ]</i>

37:14.902 --> 37:16.837
it's either a wrong number
or the hospital.

37:16.904 --> 37:20.207
In either case,
I don't wanna know.

37:20.274 --> 37:23.243
<i>[ Ringing continues ]</i>

37:24.278 --> 37:26.213
Oh, no.
Oh, yes.

37:26.280 --> 37:28.182
Ah.

37:32.252 --> 37:35.389
Hello?
Yeah, just a minute.

37:35.456 --> 37:37.825
<i>No. Ah. Who is it?
Jack.</i>

37:37.891 --> 37:40.260
I don't know.

37:44.865 --> 37:47.701
Hello. Mr. Lukovic.

37:49.803 --> 37:53.107
<i>No, I can't.
I'm in the middle
of my dinner.</i>

37:54.975 --> 37:58.979
Mr. Lukovic, I can't come over
every time one of your friends
has a problem.

37:59.046 --> 38:02.583
<i>Either bring him to the hospital
or find yourself a regular g.P.</i>

38:02.649 --> 38:04.651
Okay? I'm hanging up now.

38:04.718 --> 38:06.754
Bye.

38:06.820 --> 38:08.789
Good-Bye.

38:21.835 --> 38:23.837
Well?

38:23.904 --> 38:26.006
Well, your friend is very Old.

38:26.073 --> 38:28.041
His heart is failing.

38:28.108 --> 38:30.911
He should be in the hospital
so we can watch him.

38:30.978 --> 38:32.913
You know about medicine,
Dr. Morrison,

38:32.980 --> 38:37.050
but what you don't know
about people could
fill up fenway Park.

38:37.117 --> 38:40.888
He wants to die in the same bed
he's slept in for 40 years.

38:40.954 --> 38:43.390
Sit down.
Have a cup of coffee.

38:43.457 --> 38:46.693
It'll warm you up before
you go into all that rain.

38:49.163 --> 38:52.299
There's a fellow two blocks
around the corner
needs you to look in on him.

38:52.366 --> 38:55.235
I can't.
I'm on call tonight.

38:56.437 --> 38:58.772
It'll take you a minute
or two, tops.

38:58.839 --> 39:02.443
I can't be late.
I'm covering for another doctor.

39:03.677 --> 39:06.413
This man's in a wheelchair,
paralyzed.

39:06.480 --> 39:09.049
Mr. Lukovic,

39:09.116 --> 39:12.219
I think it's a terrific thing
that you're so concerned
about your neighbors.

39:12.286 --> 39:16.123
But I can't make any more
house calls for you.

39:16.190 --> 39:20.327
They're dangerous
for the patient
as well as for the doctor.

39:20.394 --> 39:23.730
In the time it takes for me
to get through traffic
and get over here,

39:23.797 --> 39:25.999
I could be seeing five or six
people in the hospital.

39:26.066 --> 39:29.737
Used to be,
people went to the hospital
because they had to.

39:29.803 --> 39:33.207
Now they get a sliver
in their big toe,
and they're lying in traction.

39:33.273 --> 39:37.678
Do you know
who that man is in there?
He drove the coal wagon.

39:37.745 --> 39:41.749
He'd come to your home,
open the chute, and the coal
would fall down into the cellar.

39:41.815 --> 39:45.519
It was filthy work,
but every home
was warm in the wintertime.

39:45.586 --> 39:48.722
Coal Wagons.
Before your time.

39:48.789 --> 39:50.724
Things used to be different.

39:50.791 --> 39:54.128
The fish man
would come around to each block
with that day's freshest catch.

39:54.194 --> 39:56.764
No frozen fish sticks.
And the vegetable man...

39:56.830 --> 39:58.766
with the big voice,
yelling, "Strawberries!"

39:58.832 --> 40:01.869
and the bread man,
they came to your home.

40:01.935 --> 40:06.106
They were people you knew,
people you could rely on.

40:06.173 --> 40:10.177
Forget about fancy tests
and little green Pills.

40:10.244 --> 40:12.880
Give your patients a little
attention, some compassion.

40:12.946 --> 40:15.883
That's what they need.
We do that
at the hospital.

40:15.949 --> 40:18.218
All over this city
there are shut-Ins, old people,

40:18.285 --> 40:20.220
sick people,
people who live alone.

40:20.287 --> 40:23.757
They don't have a lot
of money or INSURANCE
or unions to protect them.

40:23.824 --> 40:26.827
They don't have cars
to get around.
And some of them are afraid...

40:26.894 --> 40:28.829
to go outside,
of what's wrong with them.

40:28.896 --> 40:30.831
Afraid to even admit
that they're sick.

40:30.898 --> 40:33.734
That's a lot of people, Doctor.
Who's going to
take care of them?

40:33.801 --> 40:38.005
I don't know.
But I can't.

40:38.072 --> 40:43.343
In my time,
men became doctors because
it was a calling from God.

40:43.410 --> 40:46.613
But, no,
you doctors today,

40:46.680 --> 40:49.883
you're spoiled,
you're selfish.

40:49.950 --> 40:51.919
You might as well be a lawyer
or an accountant.

40:54.121 --> 40:56.523
Mr. Lukovic, I've got
to get to the hospital.

41:00.894 --> 41:04.598
Please, don't call me again.

41:14.608 --> 41:16.510
Ah!

41:18.245 --> 41:20.180
Who wants to try it?
Dr. Ehrlich?

41:20.247 --> 41:22.382
No, I can't.
Oh, no, it's easy.
Go ahead.

41:22.449 --> 41:24.952
No, really. My hand.
I can't.
Oh.

41:25.018 --> 41:26.987
Somebody--

41:44.371 --> 41:46.807
god!

41:46.874 --> 41:50.978
The vessels
through the PERICARDIUM
should look like this.

41:51.044 --> 41:55.082
Dr. Craig, I wanna be a surgeon.
I'm gonna be a surgeon.
The best surgeon.

41:55.149 --> 41:57.418
I appreciate all the time
you've taken with me,
and if you wanna stop,

41:57.484 --> 42:00.354
that's fine too, but I'm
gonna keep playing handball.

42:00.421 --> 42:02.356
I'm gonna be more careful.
I'll use more common sense,

42:02.423 --> 42:05.959
but tomorrow morning
at 6:30, I'm gonna be out there
on the court, same as always.

42:06.026 --> 42:08.595
Do you understand?
And I surf too.

42:08.662 --> 42:10.597
What do you want me to do,
Ehrlich, applaud?

42:10.664 --> 42:14.067
I just wanted you to know,
because after we had
our talk this morning,

42:14.134 --> 42:18.105
I started going a little flaky,
and that's definitely not
the direction I intend to go.

42:18.172 --> 42:21.308
And I'm sorry
to have bothered you,
but I'm glad I did.

42:21.375 --> 42:23.343
Good night.

42:25.145 --> 42:29.016
What can I tell you?
He's from california.

42:33.220 --> 42:35.222
Sorry I'm late, Peter.
No problem.

42:35.289 --> 42:37.658
It's been real slow
in here tonight.

42:37.724 --> 42:40.327
How's Megan?
She's fine.

42:40.394 --> 42:42.863
She's gonna be all right.

42:42.930 --> 42:44.932
Look, I know it's none
of my business--

42:44.998 --> 42:48.235
You're right. It isn't.

42:48.302 --> 42:51.739
It was an accident, Peter.
It could've happened to anyone.

42:51.805 --> 42:55.242
I've been calling home
in the middle of the afternoon
every day for a year now,

42:55.309 --> 42:58.245
and I've been wishing that
Myra wouldn't answer the phone.

42:58.312 --> 43:00.314
I've been wishing
she wasn't even there.

43:00.380 --> 43:03.517
I've been wishing this
whole thing was just a dream,
but it's not.

43:03.584 --> 43:05.953
I mean,
she does answer the phone.

43:06.019 --> 43:07.955
And the next thing I know,
we get to arguing.

43:08.021 --> 43:10.491
Usually about money.
Yesterday, she was upset...

43:10.557 --> 43:12.593
because there was a sale
on sneakers at Jordan Marsh,

43:12.659 --> 43:14.595
and I didn't have enough
for Megan to get a pair.

43:14.661 --> 43:16.997
Listen, man, I want Megan
to have sneakers too.

43:18.665 --> 43:21.535
I can remember
when Myra couldn't wait
for me to get home at night.

43:21.602 --> 43:25.672
And now she can't stand
for me to touch her.

43:25.739 --> 43:28.475
Uh, just the sound of my voice--

43:31.678 --> 43:34.181
We haven't made love since
She was pregnant with Timothy.

43:35.949 --> 43:37.885
Jack, there's a call
for you on 51.

43:37.951 --> 43:40.821
Mr. Lukovic.
[ sighs ]

43:40.888 --> 43:43.557
tell him I'm not here.
All righty.

43:45.726 --> 43:48.262
I guess I'd better be
getting on home.

43:48.328 --> 43:52.132
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>

44:00.240 --> 44:02.209
<i>[ door opens ]</i>

44:10.250 --> 44:12.519
Megan ate all her supper.

44:12.586 --> 44:14.588
She went right to sleep.

44:14.655 --> 44:16.623
All the excitement, I guess.

44:17.791 --> 44:20.194
You hungry?

44:20.260 --> 44:22.229
There's meat loaf
on the counter.

44:24.198 --> 44:26.967
Did you hear me?

44:27.034 --> 44:29.770
I said, there's meat loaf!
Did you hear me?

44:31.872 --> 44:34.541
Pick that up.
Pick it up yourself!

44:34.608 --> 44:37.578
<i>[ Objects clattering ]
you don't give me
anything but trouble.</i>

44:37.644 --> 44:39.613
You give me nothing
but trouble and pain.

44:39.680 --> 44:42.082
Our little girl--
don't even talk
to me about that!

44:42.149 --> 44:44.384
Because you're upstairs
in the middle of the
afternoon taking a nap!

44:44.451 --> 44:46.386
You're damn right!
I was exhausted!

44:46.453 --> 44:48.388
Exhausted from what?
From you.

44:48.455 --> 44:50.524
From being saddled with the life
of two children and dead Air.

44:50.591 --> 44:52.826
'cause that's what you are!
You are dead air!

44:52.893 --> 44:55.662
Shut up! Shut up!
Dead Air! That's--

44:59.433 --> 45:03.170
I'm sorry. Okay.
Listen to me. Listen.

45:07.341 --> 45:11.545
Uh, I'm gonna--
I'm gonna get outta here
for a little bit.

45:11.612 --> 45:13.680
No, you're not, Peter.

45:13.747 --> 45:16.884
This time, I'm leaving.

45:16.950 --> 45:19.887
For once,
you stay and you deal with it.

45:41.442 --> 45:43.377
Mr. Lukovic?

45:43.444 --> 45:45.412
He stopped breathing.

45:53.287 --> 45:55.322
[ chattering, indistinct ]

46:01.495 --> 46:06.733
- We give him
some intracardiac epi?
- Epi.

46:34.895 --> 46:37.231
Come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

46:37.297 --> 46:39.266
One more time.
Stand Clear.

46:44.505 --> 46:46.774
[ chattering ]

46:48.776 --> 46:54.014
<i>Mr. Lukovic, your friend's
gonna be all right.</i>

46:54.081 --> 46:57.251
You bastard!
I said he'll be okay.

46:57.317 --> 46:59.753
He could've died
because you didn't come!

46:59.820 --> 47:02.156
He went through all this pain
just now because of you.

47:02.222 --> 47:04.191
Because you didn't come
when I called.

47:04.258 --> 47:06.760
You selfish, lazy--
That's enough, all right?

47:06.827 --> 47:08.796
I've heard enough.

47:09.830 --> 47:11.799
When am I gonna learn?

47:11.865 --> 47:15.436
Every time I stick my neck out,
I end up regretting it.

47:19.573 --> 47:23.577
Don't you see,
if you hadn't brought him in
here, he'd be dead now?

47:25.979 --> 47:27.948
So don't give me that...

47:28.015 --> 47:31.185
about how rotten I am
and how this world stinks!

47:31.251 --> 47:35.722
It was different in your time.
I know it's changing.

47:35.789 --> 47:38.559
It's changing too fast.

47:38.625 --> 47:41.562
And I know it's terrifying
for you.
It terrifies me too.

47:41.628 --> 47:44.331
I'm gonna be a father.
I have to bring my children
into this world.

47:44.398 --> 47:47.835
I don't wanna be left behind
any more than you do.

47:49.470 --> 47:53.607
But it's not my fault,
so don't lay it on my shoulders.

47:56.477 --> 47:58.412
Okay.

47:58.479 --> 48:01.281
I won't call you again.

48:44.825 --> 48:45.993
[ mews ]
